Recent builds of EmacsFromCVS snapshots for Fedora 8 and 9:

* http://people.redhat.com/coldwell/emacs/repo/fedora/

To install the repository run this RPM command.

  $ sudo rpm -ihv http://people.redhat.com/coldwell/emacs/repo/fedora/emacs-release-23-1.fc8.noarch.rpm
  Retrieving http://people.redhat.com/coldwell/emacs/repo/fedora/emacs-release-23-1.fc8.noarch.rpm
  warning: /var/tmp/rpm-xfer.NMeUQp: Header V3 DSA signature: NOKEY, key ID 852e052f
  Preparing...                ########################################### [100%]
     1:emacs-release          ########################################### [100%]

To upgrade to a snapshot of Emacs, run

  $ sudo yum update emacs

To install emacs alongside your already installed stable Emacs, use yumdownloader and RPM.

  $ yumdownloader emacs{,-el,-common}
  $ sudo yum install dejavu-fonts m17n-lib
  $ sudo rpm -ihv --replacefiles emacs{,-el,-common}-*.rpm

To build your own Fedora package from the CVS sources:

Make a sandbox to build RPMs:
# ##mkdir ~/rpmbuild##
# ##cd ~/rpmbuild; for dir in /usr/src/redhat/*; do mkdir $(basename ${dir}); done##
# Write the following file to ##~/.rpmmacros##
{{{
 %packager       Your Name <name@email>
 %_topdir        %(echo $HOME)/rpm
}}}

Roll your own snapshot of EmacsFromCVS:
# Download a copy of the CVS repository
# Run ##EMACS=/usr/bin/emacs ./make-dist --snapshot ## from your copy of the repository

Get a Fedora source (src) package for Emacs:
# yumdownloader --source emacs
# Save it in ##~/rpmbuild/SRPMS##

Install the build dependencies for the source package.
# yum-builddep emacs-22.1-1.fc7
# Run ##rpmbuild --rebuild --nobuild ~/rpmbuild/SRPMS/emacs-22.1-1.fc7.src.rpm##

Modify the package:
# Copy your snapshot file (example: ##emacs-21.1.50.tar.gz##) to ##~/rpmbuild/SOURCES##
# Modify ##~/rpmbuild/SPECS/emacs.spec## and update the version number to the snapshot version (here: ##21.1.50##).
# Make any other changes:
** Turn off legal paranoia for TetrisMode by changing the %paranoia variable to `0'.
** Add a changelog entry with `C-c C-e'.

Build and install the RPMs:
# rpmbuild -bb ~/rpmbuild/SPECS/emacs.spec
# rpm -Uhv ~/rpmbuild/RPMS/i386/emacs{,-el,-common}-22.1.50-1.i386.rpm

To allow `find-function' to visit a "built-in function in 'C source code'", set the following in your .emacs.

  (setq find-function-C-source-directory "~/rpmbuild/BUILD/emacs-21.1.50/src/")

